    "notes": "Stellar Phase 2 curated 2026-05-30 under curation-data-contract (Tier 1 inversion fix; M dwarf regime, very different from the FGK hosts). AU Mic is a ~22 Myr Beta Pic moving group M1 Ve flare star. RADIUS IS A DOCUMENTED DIVERGENCE: the community-standard 0.75 Rsun traces to White et al. 2019, which exists ONLY as an unrefereed AAS conference abstract (no journal paper, no arXiv); the only refereed interferometric radius is Gallenne 2022 VLTI/PIONIER (theta_LD 0.825 +/- 0.033stat +/- 0.038sys mas -> R 0.862 +/- 0.052 Rsun), recommended per the contract refereed-interferometry priority. Donati 2023 infers R 0.78-0.82 from L+Teff (between the two, supporting the larger value). MASS DIVERGENCE: Plavchan 2020 PMS-isochrone 0.50 +/- 0.03 (community standard, propagated to all planet papers; Wittrock 2023 0.51 agrees) recommended over Donati 2023 Dartmouth-isochrone 0.60 +/- 0.04. Teff = Cristofari 2023 SPIRou atmospheric fit 3665 +/- 31 K ([M/H] +0.12 +/- 0.10, [alpha/Fe] 0.00 +/- 0.04, log g 4.52, with magnetic fields modelled); Donati 2023 V-I color gives 3700 +/- 70. Luminosity = Donati 2023 log(L/Lsun) = -0.99 +/- 0.01 -> 0.102 Lsun (M_bol 7.22 + BC + distance); Plavchan 2009 SED gives 0.09 +/- 0.02. Age = Mamajek & Bell 2014 Beta Pic MG 23 +/- 3 Myr (median of F/G-star isochrones 22 +/- 3 Myr reconciled with the Li-depletion-boundary age; the oft-cited ~12 Myr kinematic/expansion age is explicitly rejected). [M/H] +0.12 +/- 0.10 ~ [Fe/H] since [alpha/Fe]=0 (Cristofari 2023). Rotation = Plavchan 2020 TESS 4.86 +/- 0.01 d (Messina 2017 4.86 +/- 0.02, Klein 2021 / Donati 2023 4.83-4.86 d corroborate). Activity = Tsikoudi & Kellett 2000 ROSAT quiescent Lx 2.24e29 erg/s (0.1-2.4 keV); with L 0.102 Lsun (3.90e32 erg/s) this is log(Lx/Lbol) ~ -3.2, near the saturation limit for active M dwarfs. Strong magnetic field for the Phase 3 magnetic axis: small-scale <B> = 2.61 +/- 0.05 kG, large-scale 550 +/- 30 G (Donati 2023 SPIRou ZDI). NEXXUS (Schmitt & Liefke 2004) does NOT contain AU Mic (G/K sample) -- the '2.51e29 from NEXXUS' web claim is wrong; Tsikoudi & Kellett 2000 used instead."
  }
